This high-availability cloud architecture is designed for resilience, scalability, and fault tolerance. Traffic is distributed through a load balancer across multiple availability zones, while auto-scaling groups ensure applications can handle demand spikes.
The data layer uses replicated databases for redundancy, and shared services like monitoring, backups, security, and access control strengthen reliability.
The result is a cloud environment that remains available even during failures, ensuring business continuity and performance.